    "of papers he/she likes.",
    "In case extra text is provided, the system will extract more keywords and them to the bow created previously.",
    "Algorithm 1 Stage B.",
    "Creation of the user's personalized paper collection Require: The products of AMiner dataset's pre-processing & user's input Ensure: The personalized paper collection for the user 1: take user input 2: if DOI is provided then 3: save papers to paper collection & retrieve fos of these papers 4: end if 5: if text from papers is provided then 6: keywords extraction 7: end if 8: K-means model cluster recommendation for the user 9: for fos in the recommended cluster do 10: calculate cosine similarity: user's keywords & fos bow 11: end for 12: sort fos in similarity descending order & retrieve fos over the threshold 13: for fos in expanded fos-list do 14: retrieve all papers and add them to the full paper collection 15: end for 16: filter the full paper collection with the publication year 17: while total Papers ≤ 40, 000 do 18: add papers from various fos-lists 19: end while 20: while total Papers ≤ 30, 000 do 21: if highest cited bias is ON then 22: add highest cited papers to the final paper collection 23: else 24: add most relevant papers to the final paper collection 25:end if 26: end while 27: return the personalized paper collection for the user Using the K-means model that was created at Stage A, the system makes a cluster recommendation for the keywords assigned to the user; i.e., the system assigns the user's keywords (bow) to a fos-cluster.The system calculates the cosine similarity value on pairwise basis between the user input keywords and every fos in the recommended cluster (all fos already have a bow-list of keywords-from Stage A) and accumulates the best similarity fos-list for the user.",
    "The system rejects fos with similarity equal to zero; then, it retrieves the fos with top similarity, to create the \"best similarity fos-list\", in one of the following ways:• 1st version The system retrieves the fos with the top 10% similarity (starting point) and increases the percentage until the fos-list reaches the maximum threshold of 300 fos; the parameter top similarity percentage is set initially to 0.1, increases gradually and never exceeds 0.6."
